objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To compare the overall survival (OS) of nivolumab to sorafenib in subjects with advanced HCC who have not received prior systemic therapy.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 1
objectives.text: To compare the objective response rate (ORR) of nivolumab to sorafenib. ORR will be determined from assessment by a blinded independent central review (BICR) based on RECIST 1.1.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 2
objectives.text: To compare progression free survival (PFS) of nivolumab and sorafenib. PFS will be determined from assessments by a blinded independent central review (BICR) based on RECIST 1.1

objectives.name: Secondary Objective 3
objectives.text: To evaluate the relationship between tumor PD-L1 expression and efficacy

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: evaluating the correlation of tumor inflammation with efficacy

endpoints.name: Overall Survival (OS)
endpoints.text: OS is defined as the time from the date of randomization to the date of death due to any cause in all randomized subjects. Subjects who are alive will be censored at the last known alive dates.

endpoints.name: Objective Response Rate (ORR)
endpoints.text: ORR, as determined based on BICR-assessed tumor response according to RECIST 1.1, is defined as the proportion of all randomized subjects whose best overall response (BOR) is either a CR or PR.

endpoints.name: Progression-Free Survival (PFS)
endpoints.text: PFS is defined as the time from the date of randomization to the date of the first objectively documented tumor progression as assessed by BICR according to RECIST 1.1 or death due to any cause.

endpoints.name: PD-L1 expression
endpoints.text: The objective of evaluating the relationship between PD-L1 expression and efficacy will be measured by efficacy based on PD-L1 expression. Definition of PD-L1 expression will be described in the SAP.

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand (OS)
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with advanced hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have not received prior systemic therapy (All randomized subjects) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (HR) estimated via stratified Cox proportional hazards model.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study drug due to toxicity or other reasons

intercurrentEvents.name: Subsequent anti-cancer therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Initiation of new systemic or local anti-cancer therapies after study drug

estimands.treatment: Nivolumab 240 mg IV every 2 weeks vs Sorafenib 400 mg PO BID
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with advanced hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have not received prior systemic therapy (All randomized subjects)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Overall Survival (OS), defined as the time from the date of randomization to the date of death due to any cause
estimands.summaryMeasure: Hazard ratio (HR) estimated via stratified Cox proportional hazards model

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand (ORR)
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with advanced hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have not received prior systemic therapy (All randomized subjects) Summary measure: Odds ratio estimated via Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel (CMH) test.

intercurrentEvents.name: Subsequent anti-cancer therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Initiation of subsequent anti-cancer therapy prior to documented progression

estimands.treatment: Nivolumab 240 mg IV every 2 weeks vs Sorafenib 400 mg PO BID
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with advanced hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have not received prior systemic therapy (All randomized subjects)
estimands.variableOfInterest: Objective Response Rate (ORR), defined as the proportion of subjects with a BOR of CR or PR per BICR RECIST 1.1
estimands.summaryMeasure: Odds ratio estimated via Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel (CMH) test

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand (PFS)
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with advanced hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) who have not received prior systemic therapy (All randomized subjects) Summary measure: Hazard ratio (HR) estimated via stratified Cox proportional hazards model.
